# Create Intelligence & Intent Constitution™ (131)

**Full document:** `docs/constitution/131_CREATE_INTELLIGENCE_AND_INTENT_CONSTITUTION.md`

**Binding product law** for Create intent. Understand what the member wants to accomplish — not keyword match. Users never learn to “talk to the system.”

## Mission

Infer the user’s goal, not just their words. Outcomes → intentions → artifacts.

## Conflict rules

- **128** wins on complexity / architecture exposure / ADHD certification  
- **130** One Creation Rule — never silently create Work  
- **131** governs how intent is understood before confirmation  

## Fifteen rules (summary)

1. Intent before artifact — flyer for workshop = promotional deliverable, not Workshop Plan  
2. Offer smart alternatives when confidence &lt; ~95% — most likely + also considered  
3. Never make users rewrite  
4. Intent categories first (document/project/plan/strategy/campaign/communication/deliverable/business asset/event), then Work Type  
5. Recognize relationships — NEW vs supporting EXISTING  
6. Suggest before asking again — “I think you meant one of these”  
7. More Ways to Start calm — ≤3 visible decision layers  
8. One search, many results  
9. Context beats catalogs  
10. Navigation should confirm location  
11. Empty states match reality — Continue Working disappears if none  
12. Confidence drives behavior — VH recommend / medium 2–4 options / low one question / never silent guess  
13. Learn from corrections (V1 hooks; Intent Memory™ future)  
14. Measure success = correct work on first attempt  
15. Certification gates — all must pass before Create intent work is complete  

## Confidence bands (Rule 12)

| Band | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| Very high | Recommend · confirm Yes / Choose something else |
| Medium | Most likely + also-considered options |
| Low | One clarifying question |
| Any | Never silent Work creation |

## Before shipping Create intent / Begin / catalog routing

- [ ] Intent before artifact (promo for event ≠ event plan)?  
- [ ] Medium confidence surfaces alternatives?  
- [ ] Confirm still required before Work exists (130)?  
- [ ] Continue Working hidden when empty?  
- [ ] More Ways ≤3 decision layers?  
- [ ] No architecture / Work Type jargon in member copy (128)?  

## Intent Memory™

Per-member pattern learning is a **future capability**. V1 may keep correction-ready hooks only. Do not build a new durable preference store without Spec 112 permission paths.

